value.0: Fashioned from polished copper wirework and lacquered planks, this door offers little privacy or security, but it is a popular design in many noble households all the same.

A double of curved panels forms an air-tight door. The transparent panes are of utmost curious material, neither liquid nor solid, but as strong and resistant than any treated iron and steel known to man.

TC-22 blaster rifles are blaster rifles used by the Brotherhood of Darkness in the New Sith Wars. Like all TC rifles, their sights were skewered slightly to one side, and over time the sights lost accuracy. Their power packs hold fifty shots. They have decent blasting power and range.

A blaster is a ranged weapon that fires bursts of particle beam energy called blaster bolts from a replaceable power cell. The most commonly used weapon in the Galaxy, blasters' intense beams consisting of compacted high-energy particles and intense light can kill or paralyze their target, depending on their setting.

The BlasTech DL-22 Blaster Pistol is designed as a response to the MerrSonn DD6 weapon. The gun's barrel used a higher-grade focusing crystal to increase the damage dealt by the weapon's blasts, at the expense of the gun's stun setting. The DL-22 is held in high regard by those who prefer to customize their weapons.

The BlasTech DL-18 blaster pistol is a cheap weapon commonly and currently in use, in the Galatic Civil War.

Weapons of this make are common on Tatooine (several of Jabba the Hutt's skiff guards use DL-18 pistols), especially in the infamously violent city of Mos Eisley; hence, the model is sometimes nicknamed the "Mos Eisley Special".

A modified DH-17 pistol, the BlasTech DH-23 "Outback" pistol was built with one principle in mind durability.

Although the DH-23 is inferior to the DH-17 in several respects, including range and stun capability, the weapon featured a more effective heat shroud and tighter construction, making it difficult to break or damage.

The CR-2 blaster pistol is a basic yet durable heavy blaster pistol used by the Royal Naboo Security Forces. They are famous for being able to deflect off certain surfaces yet penetrate armor.

The CR-2 blaster was a basic blaster design created by the little-known Corellian Arms corporation, and was the first mass-produced version of the modern blaster weapon introduced on Naboo. The CR-2 primarily fired bolts of charged plasma energy, but a secondary firing mode allowed the weapon to discharge electrical bolts capable of stunning most living targets. The CR-2 pistol became an antique on most Core Worlds long before the Naboo Security Forces adopted it as the standard-issue sidearm for its Security Guards and police officers.

The Geonosian carbine is the carbine version of the Geonosian sonic blaster.

The Kalranoos carbine is a hybrid design based on the Geonosian carbine.

Power paks or power cells provide energy for many vehicles, and small blaster weapons. Most power cells contain concentrated amounts of gases that, when heated, form plasma. In small blasters, power cells are used to create blaster bolts that are not nearly as powerful as blasters using a combination of magazines containing gases (that after being heated would change into plasma) and proper Blaster power packs. A small power cell could be used to power a prosthetic without the need for recharging.

The Czerka 84-U hunting rifle is a weapon produced by Czerka Arms.

Wam Lufba found this rifle when he was thrown into the rancor pit in Jabba's Palace. He used it to escape certain death.
